      "side": 1,
      "message": "let\u0027s add several additional tests\n\nDevice index boundary - Call FTL_WRITE_SECT with device_index \u003e\u003d device_count and verify it fails gracefully rather than corrupting memory.\n\nObject isolation across devices - Create object with same object_id on devices 1 and 2, write different data to each, read back and verify they are independent. Currently no test writes the same object ID to two devices.\n\nDevice 2 read verification in Device Isolation -  currenly device 2 is written but never read-verified in the isolation test.\n\nConcurrent reads across devices - All parallel tests only cover writes. A parallel read test after a known write would verify read-path isolation.",
